<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-22T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-22T15:00:00-05:00" n="20" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Conference W And PW/1–2245:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-22T16:00:00-04:00">January 22, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 11:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>54. Your circular January 19, midnight. I have not encouraged
                                    Chiriani<note n="26" xml:id="d20fn26">Horacio Chiriani, Minister
                                    for Foreign Affairs.</note> to submit specific requests for
                                economic aid during the conference at Mexico. Paraguay may be
                                expected to introduce or support measures capable of continental
                                application which would be helpful to Paraguay such as assistance in
                                construction of Pan American Highway, additional gasoline quotas for
                                highways newly constructed with American financial aid and
                                assistance to immigrants. These topics were mentioned on pages 3 and
                                4 of my despatch 440, January 9.<note n="27" xml:id="d20fn27">Not
                                    printed.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>If other countries are being encouraged to present specific requests
                                at Mexico City I should like to be promptly informed so that
                                Paraguay may have the opportunity of doing the same.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>